@using Budgeter.Helpers

@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home Page";
    var usersHelper = new UsersHelper();
}



<div class="col-md-offset-2 col-md-8">
    <div class="tile">
        <h1 class="center">Welcome to Money Management Software</h1>

        <div id="QuickStart">
            <h2>Quick Start Guide:</h2>
            <label>MMS makes it easy to set budgets and track whether your spending is being kept within the budget parameters you have set.</label>
            <ol id="tutorialIndex">
                <li>Log In or Register (Upper right corner). <button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-xs white" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#Login">Register/Login/Create Household VIDEO</button></li>
                <li>
                   @if (Request.IsAuthenticated && !usersHelper.HaveHousehold())
                    {
                        <span> Create a household by </span>@Html.ActionLink("CLICKING HERE", "Create", "Households") <span>...or use the link in the upper right corner.</span> 
                   }
                   else
                   {
                      <span>You have created a household so move on to step 3.</span>
                   }
                </li>
                <li>After you create a household, you should create a budget and add Budget Items. <button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-xs white" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#AddAccount">Add Bank Account and Create Budget VIDEO</button></li>
                <li>After that, add bank account(s)</li>
                <li>You then start to enter transactions. Every transaction has the option to be linked to a budget item.<button id="VideoTutorial" type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-xs white" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#Transactions">Entering Transactions VIDEO</button></li>
                <li>At any time after you create a household, you can invite other people to join, or manually enter them. <button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-xs white" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#AddMembers">Add Household Members VIDEO</button></li>
                <li>The charting feature allows you to make a quick visual assessment of your budget and spending. <button type="button" class="btn btn-info btn-xs white" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#Charts">Using the Charts VIDEO</button></li>
                <li>Everything can be accessed from either the My Households view or in the left-side nav-bar.</li>

            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


